projects.graph.utils

Class PriorityQueueNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • projects.graph.utils.PriorityQueueNode

  • public class PriorityQueueNode
extends java.lang.Object

    PriorityQueueNode is a class that describes the nodes held by the PriorityQueue instance used in Graph.shortestPath(int, int). PriorityQueueNode instances also contain information about the order that a node was created and inserted into the priority queue, to help break ties in FIFO order.

    See Also:
    Graph, Graph.shortestPath(int, int), PriorityQueue

        public PriorityQueueNode(int node,
                         int distance,
                         int order)
        Simple constructor. As a side effect, stores the index of insertion into the container priority queue.
        Parameters:
        node - The node id.
        distance - The distance between the source node and the provided node.
        order - The creation order of this PriorityQueueNode. Useful for breaking ties in the container priority queue.

      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object o)

        Type-safe equality method that only checks for equality of node (after the runtime class check). To be clear, two PriorityQueueNode instances will be considered equal if they contain the same node id. We do not care about weight and order for equality considerations.
